\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Chunk</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ByteArray\">ByteArray</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> (<a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionName\">Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionName</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue\">Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue</a></span>)</span> → <a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk\">Std.Http.Chunk</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.mk","kind":"ctor","line":156,"name":"Std.Http.Chunk.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Data/Chunk.lean#L156-L184"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Chunk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Represents a chunk of data with optional extensions (key-value pairs).\n\nThe interpretation of a chunk depends on the protocol layer consuming it:\n\n- HTTP/1.1: The zero-size wire encoding (`0\\r\\n\\r\\n`) is reserved\nexclusively as the `last-chunk` terminator. The HTTP/1.1 writer silently discards\nany empty chunk (including its extensions) rather than emitting a premature\nend-of-body signal. `Encode.encode` on a `Chunk.empty` value does produce\n`\"0\\r\\n\\r\\n\"`, but that path bypasses the writer's framing logic.\n\n- HTTP/2 (not yet implemented): Chunked transfer encoding does not exist; HTTP/2 uses DATA\nframes instead. This type is specific to the HTTP/1.1 wire format.\n\nReference: https://httpwg.org/specs/rfc9112.html#rfc.section.7.1\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk","kind":"structure","line":156,"name":"Std.Http.Chunk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Data/Chunk.lean#L156-L184"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.ofString!\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Chunk</span>.<span class=\"name\">ExtensionValue</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofString!</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue\">ExtensionValue</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Creates an `ExtensionValue` from a string, panicking with an error message if the string contains\ncharacters that cannot be encoded as an HTTP quoted-string.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.ofString!","kind":"def","line":145,"name":"Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.ofString!","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Data/Chunk.lean#L145-L152"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.ofString?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Chunk</span>.<span class=\"name\">ExtensionValue</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofString?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue\">ExtensionValue</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempts to create an `ExtensionValue` from a `String`, returning `none` if the string contains\ncharacters that cannot be encoded as an HTTP quoted-string.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.ofString?","kind":"def","line":135,"name":"Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.ofString?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Data/Chunk.lean#L135-L143"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.quote\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Chunk</span>.<span class=\"name\">ExtensionValue</span>.<span class=\"name\">quote</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue\">ExtensionValue</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Quotes an extension value if it contains non-token characters, otherwise returns it as-is.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Data/Chunk.html#Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.quote","kind":"def","line":129,"name":"Std.Http.Chunk.ExtensionValue.quote","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93